erience as an organizational psychologist, Rae André shows how these practices comprise an effective model for climate leadership. Lead for the Planet is a guide for the kind of leadership that is necessary to help us all avoid the worst of global warming and to create a clean energy future for the generations to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aClimatic changesxPrevention. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Leadership.2bisacsh  aUnited Nations sustainable development goals.  aclimate change.  acrisis.  aenergy.  afossil fuel.  ainterdisciplinary.  aleadership.  amanagement.  aplanet.  astrong.  asustainability.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753802640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487538026423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487538026.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles